{% doc %}
  @prompt
    The section has a deep charcoal background. On the right, a stunning, large-scale photo of a tortoiseshell frame sweeps across the page, its polished acetate gleaming under soft light.
    
    On the left, the text appears in crisp white. A small, letter-spaced, all-caps pre-headline reads PRECISION IN EVERY DETAIL. Below it, the main headline declares: Crafted Without Compromise.
    
    From the right side of the frame, three razor-thin, copper-gold lines extend to specific points on the glasses. Each line terminates in a tiny, precise dot on the lens or frame. The annotation text next to them clearly describes the features: "Japanese Titanium Core," "5-Barrel Hinges," and "Advanced Clarity Lenses."
    
    Below the main paragraph on the left, a single, solid black button with sharp corners invites the user to EXPLORE OUR MATERIALS →.,  Use a Full-Width Section Setting
    Most modern Shopify themes allow you to control the width of individual sections. The fix is likely a simple setting in your theme editor.
    
    Go to your Shopify Theme Editor.
    
    Click on the "Crafted Without Compromise" section on the left-hand panel to open its settings.
    
    Look for a setting named "Section width," "Layout," "Page width," or something similar.
    
    Change this setting from the default ("Boxed," "Contained," or "Standard") to "Full width" or "Full bleed."
    
    This will make the section's background and its contents span the entire width of the browser window.
    
    2. How the Design Adapts to Full Width
    Making the section full-width doesn't mean the text should stretch to the far-left edge of the screen, as that would be hard to read. Instead, the layout will be intelligently divided: the background color will fill the entire space, the image will sit flush against one edge, and the text will remain neatly contained on the other side.
    
    Here is the visual breakdown of the full-width design we're creating:
    
    Left Half of the Screen (Content):
    The deep charcoal background color stretches to the absolute left edge of the browser.
    
    Your text content (PRECISION IN EVERY DETAIL, Crafted Without Compromise., etc.) and the CTA button will sit on this background, but they will still have a comfortable left margin, aligning with the rest of your site's content for a clean, professional look.
    
    Right Half of the Screen (Image):
    The stunning macro photo of your product will now completely fill the right side of the section.
    
    It will sit flush against the top, bottom, and right-hand edge of the browser window. There will be no margin or padding around it.
    
    The annotation lines will point from the feature text towards the product, creating a seamless connection between the two halves.
    
    This technique creates a dynamic, high-end feel. It breaks the monotony of a standard layout and gives this particular section the visual weight and importance , make sire its mobile responsive 
